DIPLOMATIC ASSESSMENT
India's optimal posture is aggressive multi-vector diplomacy that keeps it off the belligerent list of all parties while maximising bilateral energy access. This requires: (1) formal diplomatic reaffirmation to Iran of India's non-belligerent status; (2) activation of SCO/BRICS collective messaging for corridor protection; (3) quiet coordination with China on shipping safety norms; (4) domestic political management of the Pakistan mediator narrative; and (5) careful messaging to the US that India's bilateral Iran engagement is a commercial necessity, not a strategic defection.

